==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|alt=彼,彼れ}}
From older ''[[かれ|kare]]'' → ''are''. Compound of {{suffix|ja|あ|tr1=a|t1=that, yon|れ|tr2=re|pos2=nominalizing suffix for demonstratives}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Pronoun====
{{ja-pos|pronoun}}

# [[distal]] [[demonstrative]], something far off [[removed]] from both speaker and listener: [[that]], [[yon]]
## ''([[deictically]])'' [[that]] one over there (far from the speaker and the addressee)
## ''([[anaphorically]])'' [[that]] one we both know (both the speaker and the addressee know)
# {{lb|ja|chiefly|derogatory}} [[third-person]] [[personal]] [[pronoun]]: [[he]], [[she]], that [[person]]
# [[you-know-what]]; a thing whose name the speaker do not want to mention
## [[sex]]
## [[cockroach]]
# {{lb|ja|archaic}} [[second-person]] [[pronoun]]: [[you]]

=====Usage notes=====
* Indicates something far off, removed from both speaker and addressee. Contrast with {{ja-r|それ}}, indicating something removed from the speaker but closer to the addressee.

